Argentine Stocks: Siderar SAIC and YPF SA Shares Advance

-- B y   B r y a n   G i b e l
-- 
2011-06-30T20:49:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/argentine-stocks-siderar-saic-and-ypf-sa-shares-advance.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 4:30 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index rose 0.2 percent to 3,360.64, its fourth
day of gains. It increased 3.4 percent during the month.  Siderar SAIC (ERAR)  ,  Argentina ’s largest steel producer,
rose 1.8 percent to 31.35 pesos, as businesses in the U.S.
unexpectedly expanded at a faster pace in June and consumer
confidence reached a 10-week high, signs that economic growth
may pick up in the second half of the year. Siderar’s products
are used in the automotive, household appliance, construction,
agriculture, packaging and galvanizing industries, both
domestically and internationally.  YPF SA (YPFD)  , the Argentine unit of  Spain ’s Repsol YPF,
climbed 2.4 percent to 189.50 pesos, as oil advanced as much as
1.1 percent and the euro climbed to the highest level in three
weeks against the U.S. currency. Crude for August delivery rose
16 cents, or 0.2 percent, to $94.93 a barrel on the  New York
Mercantile Exchange .  To contact the reporters on this story:
Bryan Gibel in New York at 
